# Task 5 - Dockerize an Application

## Objective
Containerize a simple web application using Docker and deploy it on AWS EC2.

## Tools Used
- AWS EC2
- Ubuntu
- Docker
- Nginx

## Steps Performed

1. Installed Docker on EC2.
2. Started Docker service.
3. Created index.html.
4. Created Dockerfile.
5. Built Docker image.
6. Ran Docker container.
7. Exposed container on port 8080.
8. Updated Security Group rules.
9. Accessed application through browser.

## Commands Used

```bash
docker --version
docker build -t task5-app .
docker images
docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name task5-container task5-app
docker ps
